Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Preston Library Preston Library Library Home Library Home Find Books Find Books Departments Departments Media Equipment Media Equipment Technical Services Technical Services Visitor Information Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Archives Archives Archives Home Archives Home Online Exhibits Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Civil War   New Market Give Give Close Menu General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445 Frequently Asked Questions  ATM Locations  There are two ATM machines located on Post  One is in Lejeune Hall Food Court and the second one is located in Daniel s Courtyard  Shuttle to Cameron information   The Shuttle departs from the corner of Parade Avenue and Letcher Avenue  in front of Moody Hall  and will drop off passengers at Cameron Hall  corner of Diamond and Main Street   When to change into gym uniform   Cadets should change into athletic uniform after lunch  They are required to be in their athletic uniform with name tag for the 2 00 p m  Superintendent s Welcome in Cameron Hall  Cadets should keep one set of civilian clothes  appropriate for traveling  with them and store items with their luggage  Sequence of events on Matriculation day  schedule subject to change   Matriculation  Cameron Hall 7 30 a m    11 30 a m   Matriculation Fair Crozet Hall 8 00 a m  1 00 p m   Barracks Check In  Barracks   until 1 30 p m   Superintendent s Welcome  Cameron Hall  2 00 p m   March Off  Cameron Hall  2 30 p m  Restrooms  Restroom facilities are available in Cameron Hall  Lejeune Hall and Crozet Hall  Where to put luggage  Personal items should remain in the vehicle until the Matriculation in Cameron Hall and the Matriculation Fair processes are completed  and then cadets will be allowed to check into Barracks  Can parents family friends help carry luggage to room  Yes  family members and friends are allowed into Barracks to assist their cadet with Barracks Check in  Refreshments  Bottled water will be available in Cameron Hall  Refreshments are also available in Crozet and the Third Barracks Food Court  The Parents Council tent located on the Parade Ground will also have water available  Parents Council  Information regarding the Parents Council can be found at www vmi edu parentscouncil  Where to eat lunch  Lunch will be provided for the new cadets from 11 00 a m    1 30 p m  in Crozet Hall  New cadets can eat at Crozet Hall at no charge  the cost for family members to each lunch is  9 00 for adults and children children 5 and under eat free  payment will be accepted at the door  You can also purchase tickets at the Parents Council tent in front of barracks or at the Parents Council table during the matriculation fair to cut down on your wait time in Crozet Hall  The PX in Lejeune Hall is an alternative where family members can pay to eat  It is important that new cadets eat during this time and to drink plenty of fluids with the meal  There are a numerous restaurants available in Lexington as well  It is not appropriate for new cadets to leave VMI while wearing their gym uniform  Network cable   other needs  Information Technology will have a table to answer questions as a part of the Matriculation Fair  When can rats read send email  New cadets have email access once classes begin  When can parents visit their rat  Parents are invited to attend the New Cadet Oath Ceremony at the New Market Battlefield State Historical Park in New Market  Virginia  on Sunday 6 September at 11 00 a m  After the new cadets return to Lexington  turn in their weapons  and attend an accountability formation   they can depart Post with the parents guests for dinner in Lexington  New cadets will need to return to Post NLT 10 00 p m  Parents are also encouraged to visit upon completion of football games on Saturdays  and during Parents Weekend 16 17 October  Please visit the VMI calendar at http www2 vmi edu eventcalendar  How do weekend permits work  Permits are special requests submitted by cadets through the Deputy Commandant as directed by the VMI Blue Book  rules for cadets  Rats are not normally allowed to  take  weekends during the first semester  When can rats leave campus on Parents Weekend  The Parents Weekend Brochure is available at the Parents Council table in the Matriculation Fair and is mailed to all cadet parents  Additional guidance is provided to the rats from the Commandant s Office Please visit www vmi edu parentsweekend  When can rats be picked up fly out for Thanksgiving  All cadets are allowed to leave CAD  close of academic duty  for furloughs  This means at the completion of their last academic class scheduled for that day  Cadet Ride information  The Ride Share forum allows cadets to either look for a ride or make a ride available during various breaks throughout the year  The site can be found at www vmi edu rideshare General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445  General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  Ne